name: The File of Young Kindaichi Returns
overview: High school student Hajime Kindaichi is the supposed grandson of famous private detective Kosuke Kindaichi. Visiting Hong Kong for a fashion event with Kindaichi, our hero's girlfriend Miyuki is captured by a stranger in a case of mistaken identity. The journey to save Miyuki itself leads to yet another crime case...

episodes.name: "The Hong Kong Kowloon Treasure Murder Case File 1"
episodes.overview: When a model who looks like Miyuki goes missing, Miyuki is recruited to take her place at a fashion show event in Hong Kong. Hajime and Miyuki go to Hong Kong, where they run into their friend, Saki... and Miyuki is abducted!

episodes.name: "The Hong Kong Kowloon Treasure Murder Case File 2"
episodes.overview: While surprising information about the parentage of several of the people involved is revealed, Ran is kidnapped for real and the true nature of the Poison Dragon comes to light. Ran's tattoo indicates the whereabouts of a nuclear bomb that could detonate in less than 12 hours!

episodes.name: "The Hong Kong Kowloon Treasure Murder Case File 3"
episodes.overview: While Detective Li races to find the bomb before it goes off, Kindaichi goes back to the hotel to recreate the first murder. But how can one killer account for three murders when all of the main suspects have perfect alibis?

episodes.name: "The Hong Kong Kowloon Treasure Murder Case File 4"
episodes.overview: Kindaichi unmasks the true Poison Dragon! Did Miyuki really murder three people in Hong Kong?

episodes.name: "Reika Hayami and the Uninvited Guest"
episodes.overview: Kindaichi is on a party boat with idol Hayami Reika and a lot of her other fans. He would be having a great time, too, if it weren't for the suspicious man next to him...

episodes.name: "The Alchemy Murder Case File 1"
episodes.overview: Kindaichi is on a treasure-hunting reality show with the goal to find a hidden ton of gold bullion, but he and the other contestants and staff don't realize they're being stalked by a murderous masked figure who may be an alchemist! Making matters worse is the fact that they're trapped on an isolated island with no means of communication!

episodes.name: "The Alchemy Murder Case File 2"
episodes.overview: The bodies start piling up in the mansion on a solitary island. And when one member is murdered inside of a locked room, the only possible suspect is Reika-chan?

episodes.name: "The Alchemy Murder Case File 3"
episodes.overview: The Alchemist has already committed four murders, but Kindaichi is determined that there be no more. He also wants to prove Reika-chan's innocence, since her fellow entertainers have seen fit to tie her up in the meantime. Can Kindaichi solve the twin mysteries of the locked room murder and the vanished sword?

episodes.name: "The Alchemy Murder Case File 4"
episodes.overview: Hajime uncovers the Alchemist's final trick, and then exposes the killer's identity! But what is the person's motive for brutally murdering four people in a mansion on a remote island? The answer lies within a tale of tragedy and revenge!

episodes.name: "The Prison Prep School Murder Case File 1"
episodes.overview: When Hajime is in danger of having to repeat a year, Miyuki takes him to the hellishly strict Gokumon Prep School. But even before they can get a tour, a former student is murdered there via poison. Kindaichi is on the case, but it looks to become much bigger with a study retreat taking place in a secluded area and the machinations of the Puppeteer from Hell!

episodes.name: “The Prison Prep School Murder Case, File 2”
episodes.overview: The Gokumon Prep School study retreat begins and the conditions are even harsher than Kindaichi was expecting! Not only that, he and Miyuki are put in a separate group, although they both hear hints of a group of six students who did something unforgivable in the past and now fear deadly retribution. Whose strings are the Puppeteer from Hell pulling and what is he going to make them do?!

episodes.name: “The Prison Prep School Murder Case, File 3”
episodes.overview: Chaos ensues when the bodies of four missing students are discovered murdered and positioned in grisly ways patterned after class topics. Kindaichi and Inspector Akechi collaborate by phone from their separate murder sites, but are stumped when everyone has an alibi. Will the Puppeteer from Hell have the last laugh?

episodes.name: “The Prison Prep School Murder Case, File 4”
episodes.overview: Kindaichi discovers the secret that punctures everyone's supposedly airtight alibi! He assembles both groups, explains the reasoning behind the theme murders, and calls out the identity of Sparrow, the serial murderer of six students! Except as it turns out, Sparrow is actually...

episodes.name: “The Prison Prep School Murder Case, File 5”
episodes.overview: Kindaichi reveals the identity of the second murdering Sparrow! But how did the Puppeteer from Hell convince two law-abiding people to commit serial murder? And what fate lies in store for all three criminals?

episodes.name: “Murder at 10,000 Meters, File 1”
episodes.overview: Hajime, Miyuki, Inspector Kenmochi, and Superintendent Akechi are on JAM flight 377, despite the terrorist threat received right before takeoff. They're getting closer to home when smoke suddenly fills the plane from the rear and the passengers panic, thinking it's terrorism. But things aren't what they appear as Hajime and Akechi soon find themselves trying to solve a locked-room murder case 10,000 meters in the air!

episodes.name: “Murder at 10,000 Meters, File 2”
episodes.overview: Hajime and Akechi team up to expose Captain Shida's killer... or is that killers?! Whatever the case, it leads to a situation where the plane itself (including the hundreds of passengers inside) is put in a perilous position and only one person has a shot of saving them all... but it's not Hajime!

episodes.name: “The Campground "Ghost" Case”
episodes.overview: One of Kindaichi's earliest cases is a delicate situation as the 14-year-old Hajime is on the trail of Miyuki's missing panties (and watch) from a campground. Complicating matters is the fact that Hajime himself is one of only three suspects, all of whom seem to have an ironclad alibi.

episodes.name: “Evil Spirit of the Diving Pool”
episodes.overview: In the summer of their third year in middle school, Miyuki drags Hajime to swimming school so he can finally learn, but they stumble upon drama between two divers and former best friends competing for a place at a prestigious high school. An accident happens, putting the wealthy, privileged diver into a coma. Was it down to the rumored "evil spirit of the diving pool"? Hajime suspects a more down-to-earth evil and investigates!

episodes.name: “Inspector Kenmochi, Murderer, File 1”
episodes.overview: Three years ago, a girl died after being kidnapped and abused. The three minors who were responsible are back on the street, but when one of them is shot, Inspector Kenmochi disappears. Has old man Kenmochi turned vigilante?!

episodes.name: “Inspector Kenmochi, Murderer, File 2”
episodes.overview: More evidence backs the unpopular idea that the missing Inspector Kenmochi is targeting the former minors out of revenge for what they did to the teenaged Marina three years ago. Although Hajime is convinced his old friend would never resort to vigilantism, Superintendent Akechi puts out an APB on Kenmochi on suspicion of murder!

episodes.name: “Inspector Kenmochi, Murderer”
episodes.overview: The Executioner strikes again, this time kidnapping Busujima! Can Hajime and Akechi track them down before it's too late? Plus, more evidence points to Inspector Kenmochi being the murderous vigilante!

episodes.name: “Inspector Kenmochi, Murderer, File 4”
episodes.overview: Kindaichi reveals the identity of the real Executioner at last! But what prompted his acts of bloody vengeance? Plus, a guest appearance by Hajime's nemesis!

episodes.name: “The Game Mansion Murder Case”
episodes.overview: On the bus ride home from an amusement park, Hajime and Miyuki are knocked out with a sleeping gas. They wake up to find themselves trapped in an abandoned hospital with the other bus passengers. Their only chance of getting out alive is by solving the mysterious Game Master's puzzles!

episodes.name: “The Game Mansion Murder Case”
episodes.overview: The Game Master's deadly game continues, pitting Hajime and company against one lethal trap after another. In fact, it seems like the murderous mastermind wants to do away with all of the members. Will Hajime make it out of the Game Mansion alive, let alone unmask the Game Master?

episodes.name: “The Death March of Young Kindaichi, File 1”
episodes.overview: Kindaichi goes to Hong Kong in search of Hell's Puppeteer. He attends a magic show by "Maskman," a name that the Puppeteer has used in the past. But Maskman hypnotizes him, and he starts to feel faint. When he wakes up, he's walking down the hallway of an empty building, and there's a dead body in the room behind him...
